  "Unfortunately there is, but thankfully our mental model is still mostly intact.": "",
  "In scenarios where a piece of non-React state is already being managed by some outside system –&nbsp; whether that's the browser, another library, or even your own custom data store –&nbsp;you can use React's built-in \u0000SKIP#183\u0000 hook to subscribe a component to that state without needing to redundantly duplicate it as React state in your component.": "",
